title: ‘Shock’ loophole in NSW law meant to protect children against incarceration could mean more will be locked up
summary: The Minns government has introduced a bill that allows the presumption of doli incapax, which protects children from criminal responsibility, to be overturned. This change would apply if a child is determined to have understood that their conduct was "seriously wrong." The bill aims to address concerns about child offenders and accountability.

title: House Democrat faces federal charges for allegedly stealing $5m in disaster funds – US politics live
summary: Florida Representative Sheila Cherfilus-McCormick faces allegations of misusing funds to support her 2021 campaign. The accusations suggest that she may have diverted financial resources for personal political gain. The investigation is ongoing, raising concerns about campaign finance practices.

title: Victoria to force agents to publish property reserve prices in crackdown on underquoting
summary: Victoria has implemented new "nation-first" laws requiring real estate agents to disclose the owner's reserve price within seven days of a sale. Failure to comply will result in penalties for the agents. This legislation aims to enhance transparency in real estate transactions.
